article.headline: Delaware 58, La Salle 56
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Herb Courtney scored 14 points and Delaware withstood a frenetic rally by La Salle in a 58-56 victory over the Explorers in the La Salle Invitational on Friday. Darrell Johnson added 12 points and Brian Johnson had 11 for the Blue Hens (2-9), who won their second straight game and posted their first victory in 10 career meetings in Philadelphia. Delaware was also 2-19 lifetime against the Explorers entering the game. Darnell Harris scored 12 of his 14 points in the second half for La Salle (6-5), which dropped its third consecutive game. Delaware led 55-46 with 2:59 remaining before La Salle responded with an 8-0 run -- two 3-pointers by Harris and a basket by Mike St. John -- to cut the deficit to one point, 55-54. Darrell Johnson hit one of two free throws to give the Blue Hens a 58-56 lead with 9.3 seconds left. La Salle had one last possession, but Ruben Guillandeaux missed a runner as time expired. In the first half, Delaware built a 17-point lead, 35-18, on a 3-pointer by Sam McMahon with 3:50 left before cruising to a 37-25 advantage at halftime. The Blue Hens shot 55 percent from the field (11 of 20) and converted six of 11 3-pointers.
